    "causal_summary": "The 019 deep-review packet found nine P1 defects across the mcp-coco-index stack: stale defaults, docs that contradicted production behavior, unsafe env parsing, misleading success reporting, benchmark evidence hazards, overpowering hybrid boosts, and missing RCA for query-expansion regression. These findings affect fresh installs, operator rollback instructions, reranker stability, benchmark reproducibility, and trust in search quality evidence.",
